  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0d91\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0da7\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0da7\u0dca \u0d9c\u0dad\u0dca \u0d85\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1 \u0da7\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0da7\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Those who bought tickets to come to Galle Kumari have no money and no use for the tickets",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The people are accusing the station master of Galle station of not taking action to provide relief to the passengers who were inconvenienced after the 'Gallu Kumari' train, which was running from Beliatte to Maradana, was stopped at Galle station due to the Ruhunu Kumari train derailing in Bussa area today (15) morning.",
        "Stopping the train in the middle of the train is not a weakness of the passengers, so the people asked the station master of Galle to pay for the tickets, but the station master said that he does not have the authority to do so.",
        "It is also reported that even though the police intervened to provide relief to the people, it did not work. In the first class reserved seats of the 'Galu Kumari' train, passengers had reserved seats by paying a lot of money and some people were traveling by paying more than 9000 rupees for all the family members.",
        "A large number of people, including foreigners, who were traveling in 'Galu Kumari' were inconvenienced after suddenly being informed that the train was late for a long time.",
        "In view of that situation, the passengers have to spend a lot of money and travel by bus again.",
        "When asked about this from the Secretary of the Railway Station Master's Association Mr. Kasun Chamara, he said that despite the continuous requests of the station masters to prepare a system to avoid inconvenience to the passengers in such cases, the authorities failed to do so.",
        "Railway Commercial Superintendent Mr. Vajira Polwattage tried to be contacted by phone to inquire about this situation, but he refused to answer the phone."
      ],
